gomodel:SYNGO_1802  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 6, NOS1 is localized at the postsynaptic density of the stratum radiatum of CA1synapses.\n\nLiteral:\n\"Immunogold particles coding for NOS-I concentrated over the postsynaptic density of axospinous synapses of asymmetric type (Fig. 6A). In contrast, sGCbeta labeling was concentrated over the presynaptic terminals of asymmetric axospinous synapses (Fig. 6B). Quantitative EM of randomly selected asymmetric synapses in the stratum radiatum confirmed that gold particles coding for NOS-I were predominantly postsynaptic, concentrating just cytoplasmic to the postsynaptic membrane, whereas particles coding for sGCbeta were predominantly presynaptic, concentrating 15-25 nm cytoplasmic to the presynaptic membrane (Fig. 6C). The distributions of NOS-I and sGC suggest that the two enzymes might be present on the two sides of the same synapses. To test this hypothesis, we examined sections double labeled using two sizes of gold particles. To control for possible crossreactivity (because the two primary antibodies were raised in the same species), we also studied serial single-labeled sections. Despite the vagaries of these methods, we were able to demonstrate NOS-I-positive PSDs postsynaptic to sGCbeta-positive terminals, using both techniques (Fig. 6D-F).\". Experimental description: Rat brains are used for the ultrastructural localization of NOS1 in synapses.\n\nLiteral from M&M:\n\"Tissue preparation. All procedures related to the care and treatment of animals were in accordance with institutional and National Institutes of Health guidelines. Ten male Sprague Dawley rats (200-350 gm; Charles River, Raleigh, NC)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1802" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

